thers is a compelling and timely exploration of the ideas and identities coursing between Russia, Turkey, and Ukraine – three countries determining the fate of a volatile and geopolitically pivotal part of our world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEthnic relations in literature. 0aLiterature and societyzUkrainezCrimeaxHistoryy20th century. 0aTatarszUkrainezCrimeaxHistoryy20th century. 0aTatarszUkrainezCrimeaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aUkrainian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh  aBlack Sea region.  aCrimea.  aCrimean Tatars.  aRepublic of Turkey.  aRussian literary history.  aSlavic literature.  aSoviet Russia.  aStalin.  aUkraine.  acomparative literature.  aliterature.  apoetics of solidarity.  asolidarity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753700540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487537005423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487537005/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2